diff --git a/docs/chat-mission-tracking.md b/docs/chat-mission-tracking.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1784d10
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/chat-mission-tracking.md
@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@
+# Chat mission tracking
+
+Workspace persists executable requests submitted from Chat into the shared
+Hermes Kanban.
+
+## Behavior
+
+- Informational questions remain in Chat only.
+- Executable requests create a `workspace-chat` task when `/api/send-stream`
+  starts processing.
+- The task is idempotent for a given chat send request.
+- Successful requests move to `done`.
+- Errors and interrupted requests move to `blocked`.
+- Responses that explicitly require human approval remain `blocked`.
+- A Markdown report is written to
+  `reports/chat-missions/<task-id>.md` in the selected workspace.
+
+The tracking task does not create a fake Swarm or Conductor mission. Those
+surfaces are populated only when their orchestration APIs are actually used.
+Operations continues to expose the real profile, session, cron, and usage data.
+Memory is updated only through an explicit memory write.
+
+## Human approval
+
+The tracker recognizes explicit approval gates such as:
+
+```text
+VALIDATION_HUMAINE_REQUISE: oui
+Awaiting your approval
+```
+
+The corresponding task remains in `blocked` with the reason recorded in both
+Tasks and Files.
+
+For SARL stack maintenance, `sarl-stack-steward` may audit, compare versions,
+prepare reports and staging patches, and run non-destructive tests. Compose or
+image changes, system installation, database migration, secrets, deletion,
+restart, deployment, and network exposure require human approval.
